00:27:01.786 --> 00:27:04.063
Does he have a history
of cardiac issues?

247
00:27:04.708 --> 00:27:06.021
Yeah.

248
00:27:06.536 --> 00:27:08.712
And was he taking any medications?

249
00:27:09.099 --> 00:27:10.410
He took these.

250
00:27:10.487 --> 00:27:13.962
Thanks. We're headed
to Lovelace if you'd like to follow.

251
00:27:54.269 --> 00:27:55.270
Don Juan.

252
00:28:41.586 --> 00:28:43.594
Juan Bolsa wants to see you.

253
00:28:52.775 --> 00:28:54.026
You drive.

254
00:30:01.443 --> 00:30:03.430
You I know.

255
00:30:08.380 --> 00:30:09.906
You I don't.

256
00:30:11.114 --> 00:30:13.221
Tuco's man.

257
00:30:14.518 --> 00:30:15.965
He's okay.

258
00:30:16.478 --> 00:30:18.226
Tuco's man?

259
00:30:18.441 --> 00:30:19.911
Ignacio.

260
00:30:22.704 --> 00:30:24.206
Don Hector had a stroke.

261
00:30:24.283 --> 00:30:26.140
We don't know when he will be back.

262
00:30:26.296 --> 00:30:27.902
But listen to me...

263
00:30:28.991 --> 00:30:30.781
Salamanca territory...

264
00:30:30.858 --> 00:30:33.887
stays Salamanca territory.

265
00:30:34.012 --> 00:30:35.660
Nothing changes.

266
00:30:36.968 --> 00:30:41.918
Collections continue as before.
The count must be exact.

267
00:30:42.825 --> 00:30:44.281
Anyone crosses a line...

268
00:30:44.358 --> 00:30:46.074
you stop them.

269
00:30:46.660 --> 00:30:49.184
You have a delivery
tomorrow night.

270
00:30:49.285 --> 00:30:52.140
You pick up. you package...

271
00:30:52.217 --> 00:30:53.740
you distribute.

272
00:30:54.425 --> 00:30:56.457
All as you've done before.

273
00:30:57.258 --> 00:30:58.778
Do you understand?

274
00:31:03.492 --> 00:31:05.605
You do this right...

275
00:31:07.558 --> 00:31:10.324
things could go very well for you.

276
00:31:12.813 --> 00:31:14.188
Go.

277
00:31:25.808 --> 00:31:28.840
The old bastard.
he's always been trouble.

278
00:31:30.076 --> 00:31:32.975
But he keeps his house in order.

279
00:31:34.072 --> 00:31:35.688
Gustavo.

280
00:31:39.444 --> 00:31:40.926
What do you think?

281
00:31:42.437 --> 00:31:45.707
Someone will move
against the Salamancas.

282
00:31:46.912 --> 00:31:49.707
Which brings... war.

283
00:31:51.005 --> 00:31:54.239
Which brings... chaos.

284
00:31:55.173 --> 00:31:57.324
Which brings...

285
00:31:57.530 --> 00:31:58.844
the D.E.A.

286
00:33:58.968 --> 00:34:00.428
What's up?

287
00:34:00.554 --> 00:34:02.713
It's busted again.

288
00:34:11.542 --> 00:34:13.018
It's just the chain.

289
00:34:13.649 --> 00:34:15.862
Want me to do it
or you wanna try it yourself?

290
00:34:18.946 --> 00:34:20.390
Okay.

291
00:34:21.235 --> 00:34:24.073
This is the last time. so watch.

292
00:34:24.807 --> 00:34:26.343
All right.

293
00:34:26.652 --> 00:34:30.823
So you take this. give it a little play.
right about there.

294
00:34:31.093 --> 00:34:33.909
Loop it around the big gear. yeah?

295
00:34:34.058 --> 00:34:35.832
And then...

296
00:34:37.628 --> 00:34:40.252
- That's all there is to it.
- Okay.

297
00:34:43.304 --> 00:34:46.260
- And?
- Thanks. Dad.

298
00:34:50.102 --> 00:34:52.835
Make sure Mom knows where you are.

299
00:35:35.687 --> 00:35:37.669
Hi. Denise.

300
00:35:38.294 --> 00:35:40.360
Uh. yeah. it's Barry.

301
00:35:40.443 --> 00:35:44.573
Uh. listen. could you let Mr. Eglin know
I'm gonna be late this morning?

302
00:35:45.046 --> 00:35:47.487
I might miss the staff meeting.

303
00:35:49.335 --> 00:35:52.901
No. no. Car troubles.
Probably just a dead battery.

304
00:35:53.429 --> 00:35:56.143
Yeah. I know. I know.

305
00:35:56.349 --> 00:35:58.245
Practically brand-new.

306
00:35:58.976 --> 00:36:00.862
Okay. thanks.

307
00:37:03.236 --> 00:37:06.878
Bruce had the speed. He could
kick you before you saw him move.

308
00:37:06.955 --> 00:37:10.183
- You ever watched a Liston fight?
- We're talking about what?

309
00:37:10.260 --> 00:37:13.876
- Boxing? That's something else.
- No. we're talking about a street fight.

310
00:37:13.953 --> 00:37:18.110
- Street fight? Great. so Bruce can kick.
- We're not talking a movie fight.

311
00:37:18.187 --> 00:37:21.946
- We're talking about weight. about reach.
- Boxing is a sport.

312
00:37:22.023 --> 00:37:23.977
Martial arts is life and death.

313
00:37:24.054 --> 00:37:26.284
Look. I don't care how fast you are.

314
00:37:26.361 --> 00:37:28.902
Muhammad Ali hits you.
you're going down. that's a fact.

315
00:37:28.979 --> 00:37:31.451
If he hits you.

316
00:37:31.533 --> 00:37:34.956
Bruce Lee. he knows the anatomy.

317
00:37:35.033 --> 00:37:37.141
He's got the moves.
He's gonna find an opening.

318
00:37:37.218 --> 00:37:39.964
Without power.
the opening doesn't mean squat.

319
00:37:40.041 --> 00:37:42.962
- How much does he weigh?
- I don't know. Maybe a buck-thirty.

320
00:37:43.039 --> 00:37:47.243
Ali was the heavyweight champ.
He's got a hundred pounds on Lee.

321
00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:49.386
Bruce feints for Ali's head.

322
00:37:49.463 --> 00:37:53.001
But he goes low and sweeps him
to the deck. Ali goes down hard.

323
00:37:53.078 --> 00:37:54.659
It's all over.

324
00:37:54.736 --> 00:37:56.294
Does he have a gun?

325
00:37:56.580 --> 00:37:59.714
- I'm sorry?
- Does Bruce Lee have a gun?

326
00:37:59.791 --> 00:38:03.560
Because if he doesn't.
it's Ali in three minutes or less.

327
00:38:03.697 --> 00:38:06.810
See? That's what I'm saying.
That's what I'm say...

328
00:38:07.072 --> 00:38:09.544
Hey. hold on. Wait. wait.

329
00:38:12.096 --> 00:38:14.982
Did you sign Tina's birthday card?

330
00:38:15.244 --> 00:38:18.083
- No.
- Would you mind?

331
00:38:18.668 --> 00:38:20.302
Not at all.

332
00:38:25.415 --> 00:38:28.354
- You're out of line.
- I'm saying...

333
00:38:28.431 --> 00:38:32.134
if Lee tried to sweep Ali's legs.
he'll sidestep.

334
00:38:32.211 --> 00:38:35.050
Ali was fast for his size. yes.

335
00:38:35.127 --> 00:38:37.868
But if he gets hit with a low kick.
he won't know what to do.

336
00:38:37.945 --> 00:38:40.391
I know what he'll do.
He'll do just fine.

337
00:38:40.468 --> 00:38:41.782
You're nuts.

338
00:38:41.859 --> 00:38:43.397
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

339
00:38:43.474 --> 00:38:47.159
Look. Bruce was a brawler. okay?
He gets in quick....

340
00:41:06.287 --> 00:41:07.496
I got it.

341
00:41:07.574 --> 00:41:09.159
Uh. yeah?

342
00:41:10.093 --> 00:41:12.382
Ramirez. team leader.

343
00:41:12.459 --> 00:41:13.632
Yes. sir.

344
00:41:13.715 --> 00:41:16.266
So. Ramirez. what do you
think you're up to?

345
00:41:16.343 --> 00:41:19.476
We're just pulling an order.
Something wrong?

346
00:41:19.553 --> 00:41:22.862
May I ask why none of your guys
are wearing a lift belt?

347
00:41:23.604 --> 00:41:25.231
Lift belt?

348
00:41:25.456 --> 00:41:27.704
- We don't usually...
- Stop what you're doing.

349
00:41:27.781 --> 00:41:31.370
Go to the equipment room.
You get lift belts and gloves.

350
00:41:31.517 --> 00:41:34.888
You use them.
Rules are rules. got me?

351
00:41:34.965 --> 00:41:36.490
Sure. Sure. Okay.

352
00:41:36.567 --> 00:41:38.370
On the double.

353
00:41:38.573 --> 00:41:41.534
Hey. hold up. Shut it down.

354
00:41:41.780 --> 00:41:43.355
Shut it down.

355
00:42:03.812 --> 00:42:05.543
Uh. excuse me.

356
00:42:06.101 --> 00:42:08.378
I think this belongs to you.

357
00:42:08.827 --> 00:42:12.034
Oh. my God. Ha. ha.

358
00:42:12.229 --> 00:42:15.472
Thank you.
Where did you find it?

359
00:42:15.655 --> 00:42:18.073
I need to talk to your manager.

360
00:42:19.064 --> 00:42:22.244
I waltz through security
with someone else's ID.

361
00:42:22.321 --> 00:42:24.612
Nobody gives me a second look.

362
00:42:24.806 --> 00:42:29.233
When the rightful owner shows up.
there's no facility-wide badge check.

363
00:42:29.310 --> 00:42:32.829
I find access doors left unlocked
or propped open.

364
00:42:32.906 --> 00:42:35.090
Passwords written on Post-it notes.

365
00:42:35.167 --> 00:42:39.845
Warehouse workers are using pen
and paper instead of electronic devices...

366
00:42:39.922 --> 00:42:42.014
which leaves you wide open
to pilfering.

367
00:42:42.091 --> 00:42:44.687
You got duplicate
routing numbers on cargo.

368
00:42:44.764 --> 00:42:49.456
Surveillance camera blind spots on
the north and the east side of the floor.

369
00:42:49.626 --> 00:42:53.814
Inventory documents going
into the trash instead of being shredded.

370
00:42:53.891 --> 00:42:58.413
Not to mention loading equipment
being driven at unsafe speeds...

371
00:42:58.490 --> 00:42:59.944
- and crews...
- Wait. Wait.

372
00:43:00.021 --> 00:43:03.808
- disregarding safe...
- Wait. hold on. Who are you exactly?

373
00:43:04.015 --> 00:43:05.680
Ehrmantraut.

374
00:43:05.905 --> 00:43:08.183
Security consultant.

375
00:43:09.205 --> 00:43:12.627
Well. all due respect. I don't know
anything about a security consultant.

376
00:43:12.704 --> 00:43:14.733
Well. you wouldn't. would you?

377
00:43:15.315 --> 00:43:17.589
Maybe you'd best call corporate.

378
00:43:18.086 --> 00:43:21.558
Try Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

379
00:43:40.612 --> 00:43:42.521
I'm truly sorry. Jimmy.

380
00:43:42.648 --> 00:43:45.568
Thank you. Cliff.
I appreciate that.

381
00:43:47.425 --> 00:43:48.593
Hey.

382
00:43:48.787 --> 00:43:50.540
He was a hell of a lawyer.

383
00:43:50.617 --> 00:43:52.217
Yes. he was.

384
00:43:54.534 --> 00:43:55.807
Jimmy.

385
00:43:56.708 --> 00:43:59.521
We're gonna miss him so much.

386
00:43:59.768 --> 00:44:01.365
Thank you. Brenda.

387
00:44:04.093 --> 00:44:06.865
- I'm sorry for your loss.
- Thanks. Brian.

388
00:44:10.907 --> 00:44:12.697
Jimmy. I'm so sorry.

389
00:44:12.774 --> 00:44:15.295
Oh. thanks. Appreciate that.

390
00:44:41.276 --> 00:44:42.830
Thank you.

391
00:45:20.579 --> 00:45:23.785
I-I think I owe you the truth
about Chuck.

392
00:45:25.223 --> 00:45:27.080
Those lanterns.

393
00:45:28.636 --> 00:45:32.355
He was living in that house
without electricity for two years.

394
00:45:32.432 --> 00:45:34.442
He knew how to use those lanterns.

395
00:45:34.941 --> 00:45:39.285
He was careful. I saw it. I know
you did too. There was never a problem.

396
00:45:41.480 --> 00:45:43.481
I know it's a terrible thing to...

397
00:45:47.056 --> 00:45:49.668
I don't think what happened
was an accident.

398
00:45:59.808 --> 00:46:04.215
You probably heard
Chuck was retiring from HHM.

399
00:46:05.313 --> 00:46:07.270
But that's not the truth.

400
00:46:08.733 --> 00:46:12.848
The truth is that
we had a disagreement...

401
00:46:13.263 --> 00:46:15.215
and I pushed him out.

402
00:46:15.865 --> 00:46:17.066
I made him go.

403
00:46:17.143 --> 00:46:20.569
Chuck was sick for years.
And after the bar hearing...

404
00:46:20.646 --> 00:46:22.391
The bar hearing
had nothing to do with it.

405
00:46:23.762 --> 00:46:25.024
Okay.

406
00:46:25.102 --> 00:46:28.460
The fact is.
he started getting better after that.

407
00:46:29.554 --> 00:46:33.913
He took more of an interest in the firm.
He came to work. We left the lights on.

408
00:46:34.126 --> 00:46:38.848
He was improving until the thing with
the insurance. it wasn't the bar hearing.

409
00:46:40.208 --> 00:46:41.981
The insurance?

410
00:46:42.585 --> 00:46:44.668
It was a ridiculous thing.

411
00:46:47.063 --> 00:46:48.774
I should've just let it go.

412
00:46:48.851 --> 00:46:51.184
I mean. God knows
he's done enough for me.

413
00:46:51.866 --> 00:46:54.715
But he kept pushing and I. um....

414
00:46:55.348 --> 00:46:57.152
I got my back up.

415
00:46:58.059 --> 00:47:00.109
What about the insurance?

416
00:47:00.186 --> 00:47:03.142
It was. uh. our malpractice insurance.

417
00:47:03.219 --> 00:47:05.910
They found out about Chuck's condition.
raised our rates.

418
00:47:06.838 --> 00:47:10.246
Chuck went ballistic.
He wanted to go to war.

419
00:47:10.444 --> 00:47:12.137
I drew a line.

420
00:47:12.365 --> 00:47:14.254
He wouldn't back down.

421
00:47:14.617 --> 00:47:16.199
So I forced him out.

422
00:47:21.365 --> 00:47:24.199
It never occurred to me
that I could hurt him.

423
00:47:25.201 --> 00:47:27.565
He always seemed so strong.

424
00:47:28.410 --> 00:47:30.058
But he wasn't.

425
00:47:31.660 --> 00:47:34.214
I think he did what he did
because of me.

426
00:47:42.266 --> 00:47:45.416
Well. Howard.
I guess that's your cross to bear.

427
00:48:04.896 --> 00:48:06.878
Look at her go.

428
00:48:07.462 --> 00:48:11.497
S-S-So I'm gonna make some coffee.
Anybody want some?
